WEBVTT

00:11.888 --> 00:13.431
I think
I'm losing my mind.

00:13.598 --> 00:15.225
Hello, Shadow.

00:16.267 --> 00:17.936
There are bigger sacrifices

00:18.103 --> 00:19.896
one might be asked to make

00:20.063 --> 00:22.023
than going a little mad.

00:23.733 --> 00:25.193
What's in Chicago?

00:25.360 --> 00:26.903
The hammer.

00:27.946 --> 00:32.283
If I lose, I will go with Votan
and do what he asks...

00:33.326 --> 00:34.661
And if you win?

00:34.828 --> 00:37.539
I get to knock
your brains out with my hammer.

02:54.509 --> 02:56.469
Right there.

02:56.636 --> 02:58.221
OK.

03:02.517 --> 03:04.686
Mmm!

03:06.020 --> 03:07.605
Mmm. Perfect.

03:07.772 --> 03:09.357
It's too good for them.

03:09.524 --> 03:13.194
Eight grandchildren,
each one smart as a table.

03:13.361 --> 03:15.405
Assaf with his music.

03:15.572 --> 03:17.824
He sounds like you. Yeah.

03:17.991 --> 03:21.703
No, it's too early
to fry the onions.

03:21.870 --> 03:23.955
Assaf likes them crisp.

03:25.373 --> 03:27.083
No, no, it's not perfect.

03:27.250 --> 03:29.002
More cinnamon.

03:31.796 --> 03:36.384
Assaf? I told you
no come before 5:00!

03:36.551 --> 03:38.595
And no more bringing me
your laundry!

03:38.761 --> 03:40.805
I tell you I am done
being your maid...

03:43.016 --> 03:44.601
You are in wrong floor.

03:44.767 --> 03:46.811
Black people family
is upstairs.

03:48.980 --> 03:50.648
No mistake.

03:51.816 --> 03:55.153
You are to come with me,
Mrs Fadil.

03:56.195 --> 03:58.406
You have died, Mrs Fadil.

03:59.490 --> 04:02.702
And it is time for you
to come with me.

04:03.745 --> 04:05.455
I have company soon.

04:05.622 --> 04:08.207
If you are here to rob,
then rob.

04:08.374 --> 04:10.668
There's a television,
and I...I have a phone

04:10.835 --> 04:13.171
my grandson says
is also a camera.

04:15.340 --> 04:17.800
I wish I was but a thief.

04:17.967 --> 04:20.136
I am not.

04:20.303 --> 04:21.846
I am of Death.

04:22.889 --> 04:25.391
You are dead, Mrs Fadil.

04:30.521 --> 04:33.858
- That is me?
- That is you.

04:34.025 --> 04:36.736
Your family will come soon
and find you.

04:37.820 --> 04:39.697
They will do right
by your body

04:39.864 --> 04:41.449
and bury you as is proper.

04:41.616 --> 04:43.201
They will be sad for a time,

04:43.368 --> 04:45.620
then they will find
happiness again.

04:45.787 --> 04:47.956
Your Assaf will marry
in a year

04:48.122 --> 04:50.750
and name his first daughter
for you.

04:50.917 --> 04:53.211
A bullshit middle name?

04:53.378 --> 04:56.673
A bullshit middle name.

04:56.839 --> 04:59.509
This is how
they will find me?

05:09.185 --> 05:11.229
This is a Muslim home.

05:12.313 --> 05:15.566
Why does Anubis hold out
his hand for me?

05:15.733 --> 05:18.236
It is my thanks.

05:18.403 --> 05:21.531
You were once a girl
with your own Tita.

05:21.698 --> 05:24.575
Who taught you
the ways of Egypt old,

05:24.742 --> 05:27.495
of when the Nile
was full and flooding.

05:27.662 --> 05:31.332
She told you stories
of the Wolf and the Jackal,

05:31.499 --> 05:34.627
the Red Wind,
and of the Child of Bast.

05:34.794 --> 05:37.714
- I remember.
- You do.

05:37.880 --> 05:42.051
For that,
I bring you to the Scales.

05:42.218 --> 05:43.845
Come.

05:50.685 --> 05:53.604
My family will find me.

05:55.523 --> 05:57.900
They will not try it.

05:59.986 --> 06:01.821
You taste.

06:07.910 --> 06:09.954
It is perfect.

06:11.039 --> 06:13.207
68 years.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.420
It's not much for America,

06:17.587 --> 06:22.633
but...more than my Tita
ever prayed for.

06:23.676 --> 06:25.428
Come.

07:22.735 --> 07:24.278
This is not Queens.

07:24.445 --> 07:26.697
This is not
Queens.

07:57.270 --> 07:58.813
I was using that.

07:58.980 --> 08:01.357
We shall see
if you have used it well.

08:08.531 --> 08:12.285
I was unkind to the first boy
who loved me.

08:13.327 --> 08:15.663
I stole a doll once
from my cousin.

08:15.830 --> 08:17.415
I...

08:18.624 --> 08:21.002
I tried...my best.

08:24.714 --> 08:26.424
Your best is good.

08:41.606 --> 08:44.150
Each will take you
to the Duat.

08:44.317 --> 08:46.485
The Duat has many worlds.

08:47.695 --> 08:49.071
Choose.

08:50.114 --> 08:51.741
Which has my father?

08:52.825 --> 08:54.535
He beat me,

08:54.702 --> 08:57.788
and I would like
not to see his world.

08:57.955 --> 09:00.499
Choose.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.590
You are a kind boy.

09:07.757 --> 09:10.259
You choose for me?

09:30.029 --> 09:32.281
Are you sure I do this
with you?

09:33.532 --> 09:35.326
Follow the wrong god,

09:35.493 --> 09:37.578
I do not see my Tita again.

10:56.115 --> 10:57.658
Careful!

11:08.252 --> 11:10.087
The Buffalo is waning tonight.

11:14.550 --> 11:18.387
You're Zorya Poluch...ch...

11:18.554 --> 11:20.431
The sister that was sleeping.

11:20.598 --> 11:24.393
I'm Zorya Polunochnaya, yes.

11:24.560 --> 11:26.562
And you are called Shadow.

11:32.401 --> 11:34.612
What are you
looking at up there?

11:35.654 --> 11:37.073
I was looking at that.

11:37.239 --> 11:38.783
See?

11:38.949 --> 11:40.493
The Big Dipper?

11:40.659 --> 11:42.203
Odin's Wain, they call it.

11:42.370 --> 11:44.330
And the Great Bear.

11:44.497 --> 11:46.749
It is a...thing.

11:46.916 --> 11:49.919
It's not a god. Like a god.

11:50.086 --> 11:52.213
It's a bad thing.

11:52.380 --> 11:54.298
Chained up in those stars.

11:54.465 --> 11:57.468
If it escapes, it will eat
the whole of everything.

11:57.635 --> 11:59.303
So we watch the sky...

11:59.470 --> 12:03.724
..all day, all night,
the three sisters.

12:05.434 --> 12:07.937
If he escapes,
the thing in the stars,

12:08.104 --> 12:09.522
the world is over.

12:09.688 --> 12:11.232
Like that.

12:11.399 --> 12:13.734
And people believe that?

12:13.901 --> 12:16.237
A long time ago.

12:18.030 --> 12:19.949
You're not cold?

12:20.116 --> 12:22.076
Cold doesn't bother me.

12:23.119 --> 12:24.745
This time is my time.

12:25.788 --> 12:27.957
My sisters,
they're of their times.

12:29.166 --> 12:30.668
When is your time?

12:30.835 --> 12:32.336
Your birthday?

12:32.503 --> 12:35.339
No, I...I don't want
my fortune told.

12:35.506 --> 12:37.591
My fortunes are the best.

12:38.634 --> 12:40.845
Virgins have the advantage.

12:43.639 --> 12:45.558
And now we have something.

12:49.019 --> 12:50.438
Oh.

12:50.604 --> 12:52.189
No.

12:52.356 --> 12:53.816
You have nothing.

12:53.983 --> 12:57.236
You believe in nothing,
so you have nothing.

12:58.404 --> 13:00.698
You are on a path...

13:01.740 --> 13:03.784
..from nothing to everything.

13:05.411 --> 13:08.414
You had something recently.
You lost it.

13:08.581 --> 13:12.418
- My...my wife.
- Not your wife.

13:12.585 --> 13:15.880
Did you sell your head
to Czernobog?

13:18.674 --> 13:20.384
Yeah.

13:20.551 --> 13:22.553
You keep giving away your life.

13:22.720 --> 13:25.514
You don't much care
if you live or die, do you?

13:28.058 --> 13:30.394
The world's not
what I thought it would be.

13:33.063 --> 13:34.940
You'd rather die

13:35.107 --> 13:37.985
than live in a world
with bears in the sky.

13:42.364 --> 13:44.074
I can help you.

13:44.241 --> 13:46.577
First, you must do
something for me.

13:46.744 --> 13:50.080
What is it?
Gotta fight you? Play checkers?

13:50.247 --> 13:51.957
You have to kiss me.

13:53.042 --> 13:54.835
I have not ever been kissed.

13:55.002 --> 13:57.046
I don't know if I like it.

13:57.213 --> 13:58.631
We do this now.

13:58.797 --> 14:00.299
I...

14:07.890 --> 14:11.227
Kissing is...disgusting.

14:11.393 --> 14:13.771
But...but in a nice way.

14:13.938 --> 14:18.275
Like, uh, blue cheese or brandy.

14:24.240 --> 14:25.908
Take the moon.

14:27.368 --> 14:28.744
What?

14:28.911 --> 14:31.497
Just take it. Here.

14:41.006 --> 14:44.927
Don't lose this.
Don't give it away.

14:45.970 --> 14:47.638
You've been given
protection once.

14:47.805 --> 14:49.390
You had the sun itself.

14:49.557 --> 14:51.809
I can give you the moon.

14:53.602 --> 14:55.604
It's the daughter,
not the father.

14:56.647 --> 14:58.190
Now...

14:59.233 --> 15:00.859
..you wake up.

15:14.164 --> 15:16.625
Is not sunrise yet.

15:17.835 --> 15:20.004
Enjoy your time.

15:20.170 --> 15:21.839
How about another game?

15:23.382 --> 15:25.134
Same terms.

15:25.301 --> 15:27.011
How can be same?

15:27.177 --> 15:29.513
You want me to kill you twice?

15:31.473 --> 15:34.101
Right now you only have
one blow.

15:34.268 --> 15:36.604
One is all it takes.

15:36.770 --> 15:38.314
That is...

15:39.356 --> 15:40.899
..the art.

15:43.402 --> 15:45.237
How long has it been

15:45.404 --> 15:47.364
since you last swung
a killing hammer

15:47.531 --> 15:49.116
in the stockyards, though?

15:50.367 --> 15:52.786
It's gotta be, like,
what, 20 years?

15:52.953 --> 15:54.538
30?

15:55.664 --> 15:58.334
I think you got used to
the bolt gun.

15:58.500 --> 15:59.960
I think you got weak,

16:00.127 --> 16:02.755
and I don't think
you can kill me with one shot.

16:02.921 --> 16:05.507
You could just leave me
brain-damaged,

16:05.674 --> 16:09.595
a drooling piss bag reminder
that you got old.

16:10.638 --> 16:13.766
That's not gonna do
either of us any good, is it?

16:15.059 --> 16:17.728
If you're gonna
smash my brains in,

16:17.895 --> 16:19.938
I'd rather you finish the job.

16:26.612 --> 16:29.031
I win, you come with me
and Mr Wednesday,

16:29.198 --> 16:31.158
you'll still take your shot
when we're through.

16:31.325 --> 16:32.868
But you win...

16:34.286 --> 16:37.122
..and come sunrise,
you'll take your second swing,

16:37.289 --> 16:38.957
if you need it.

16:40.918 --> 16:43.337
No-one needs to know but me.

17:00.646 --> 17:03.357
OK. Another game.

17:04.400 --> 17:07.403
You are light, I'm dark.

17:21.625 --> 17:24.253
Enough visiting. Go to bed.

17:24.420 --> 17:26.547
I'm trying to.

17:32.010 --> 17:34.555
You deserve better than this.

17:34.722 --> 17:37.641
You no like it,
you sleep on floor.

17:37.808 --> 17:39.685
Is good enough for me.

17:39.852 --> 17:41.895
You only learned
to live with less.

17:42.062 --> 17:43.605
There is food,
there is roof.

17:43.772 --> 17:45.441
What more do you need?

17:45.607 --> 17:48.360
A court to adore you.

17:50.070 --> 17:52.239
In the old country,
you were draped with pearl,

17:52.406 --> 17:54.366
loved, feared, waited upon.

17:54.533 --> 17:56.326
Excess suits you.

17:57.411 --> 18:00.080
Things will be better again
soon enough.

18:04.543 --> 18:06.420
Ahh.

18:06.587 --> 18:08.088
Your turn.

18:09.131 --> 18:10.966
Ahh.

18:12.342 --> 18:13.719
Mm-hmm.

18:13.886 --> 18:15.387
Bye-bye.

18:16.555 --> 18:18.223
In old country,

18:18.390 --> 18:22.478
I opened the gate
for my father at dusk

18:22.644 --> 18:24.480
when he returned to us,

18:24.646 --> 18:28.192
then climb into
black satin sheet.

18:29.443 --> 18:33.071
Here, I tell pretty fortune
for dollars.

18:34.573 --> 18:37.242
Now, you've never told me mine.

18:42.998 --> 18:45.751
This thing you want to do,

18:45.918 --> 18:48.253
you will fail

18:48.420 --> 18:50.923
and they will win.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.636
That's only my fortune today.

19:01.600 --> 19:05.145
Come.
Walk with me, hmm?

19:05.312 --> 19:07.231
It will rain now.

19:07.397 --> 19:09.483
Boy, will it ever.

19:09.650 --> 19:13.028
Since when were you afraid
of getting a little wet, hmm?

19:25.999 --> 19:29.044
You're playing
the same game, old man.

19:29.211 --> 19:30.587
Only get to fool me once.

19:30.754 --> 19:32.005
Shut your mouth!

19:32.172 --> 19:34.508
Still so beautiful.

19:34.675 --> 19:37.219
I thought I told
the pretty lies.

19:37.386 --> 19:40.055
You want fortune
or you want truth?

19:40.222 --> 19:42.891
Oh, I want knowledge
over comfort,

19:43.058 --> 19:44.852
over all things, always.

19:45.018 --> 19:47.771
They will kill you this time.

19:47.938 --> 19:49.648
Ahh...

19:51.984 --> 19:55.821
Do you remember
when we were young?

19:57.030 --> 19:58.574
Barely.

20:00.826 --> 20:02.911
Well, let me remind you.

20:15.465 --> 20:17.843
What have you done?

20:41.783 --> 20:44.703
I can taste you on the rain.

20:48.749 --> 20:50.834
What else can I taste?

20:51.001 --> 20:53.003
War.

21:28.872 --> 21:30.290
Alright.

21:32.376 --> 21:37.130
I'll go with Votan
to his Wisconsin.

21:40.467 --> 21:43.095
Then I'm gonna kill you.

21:45.389 --> 21:47.265
Is good?

21:52.938 --> 21:54.439
Is good.

22:46.825 --> 22:49.661
Oh, you're up. This is good.

22:50.996 --> 22:53.999
- Storm died.
- No, it hasn't.

22:54.166 --> 22:56.418
We're gonna rob a bank.

22:56.585 --> 22:58.336
You want some coffee?

23:26.323 --> 23:27.824
You best be getting on, son.

23:27.991 --> 23:30.827
Jack's Crocodile will take
a bite outta you.

23:31.870 --> 23:33.622
You won't shoot.

23:33.789 --> 23:35.749
You'll try,
but the gun will jam,

23:35.916 --> 23:38.835
or worse, it'll backfire
and you'll lose two fingers.

23:40.128 --> 23:41.797
Don't push your luck.

24:07.447 --> 24:09.741
♪..special on my mind... ♪

24:11.451 --> 24:12.869
Hey, there.

24:13.036 --> 24:15.622
You look like you've
seen better days, friend.

24:15.789 --> 24:18.959
- You OK there?
- I am not.

24:19.126 --> 24:21.795
- Where you headed?
- Wisconsin.

24:21.962 --> 24:24.131
Take you as far as Madison.
Get in.

24:24.297 --> 24:26.967
- You a rapist?
- No.

24:27.134 --> 24:30.512
- Murderer?
- Not recently. You?

24:32.097 --> 24:35.600
I got seats that tip back
if you want a good sleep.

24:40.147 --> 24:42.149
11 years sober,

24:42.315 --> 24:45.235
but I remember being
on your side of the highway.

24:45.402 --> 24:49.239
♪ We only danced
for a minute or two

24:49.406 --> 24:53.160
♪ But then she stuck close to me
the whole night through

24:53.326 --> 24:55.996
♪ Can I be fallin' in love? ♪

24:56.163 --> 24:57.539
I'm not a drunk.

24:57.706 --> 25:00.709
OK.

25:00.876 --> 25:03.879
Got a sack of cranberries
on the floor.

25:04.045 --> 25:06.173
♪..and she held my hand

25:06.339 --> 25:08.758
♪ I knew it couldn't be
just a one-night stand... ♪

25:08.925 --> 25:10.468
Don't try to touch my knob.

25:10.635 --> 25:14.598
Not my style, friend.
And not my type.

25:14.764 --> 25:16.141
But when you wake up,

25:16.308 --> 25:18.226
I might extol the virtues
of the program.

25:18.393 --> 25:19.936
Yeah, you do that.

25:20.103 --> 25:21.521
♪ I'm into something good

25:21.688 --> 25:24.149
♪ Something tells me
I'm into something... ♪

25:49.424 --> 25:51.009
That's some crazy bad luck.

26:06.399 --> 26:07.400
No.

26:07.567 --> 26:09.486
No, no, no, no, no!

26:14.532 --> 26:16.576
Fuck!

26:44.729 --> 26:46.273
Watch it!

27:17.095 --> 27:18.888
It's 11:35.

27:19.055 --> 27:21.891
My appointment was for 11:00.

27:22.058 --> 27:25.103
Mr Blanding knows you're here.

27:49.336 --> 27:50.879
Excuse me.

27:51.046 --> 27:53.423
Can you perhaps call Mr Blanding

27:53.590 --> 27:55.508
and tell him I am still waiting?

27:55.675 --> 27:57.594
He's at lunch.

27:57.761 --> 27:59.512
When will he be back?

28:16.363 --> 28:19.115
He won't be coming back.

28:20.283 --> 28:21.868
Excuse?

28:22.035 --> 28:23.536
Mr Blanding.

28:23.703 --> 28:25.622
He won't be coming back today.

28:33.838 --> 28:36.132
Can I make an appointment
for tomorrow?

28:36.299 --> 28:38.134
You have to telephone.

28:38.301 --> 28:41.346
Appointments only by telephone.

28:43.181 --> 28:44.724
I see.

28:46.476 --> 28:48.478
Why are you smiling?

28:48.645 --> 28:51.773
A salesman is naked in America
without a smile.

28:52.816 --> 28:55.110
Tomorrow I will telephone.

29:17.632 --> 29:19.884
Peak Hotel, please.

30:13.021 --> 30:14.981
Fuck! Fuck! Shit! Fuck!

30:15.148 --> 30:16.774
Oh.

30:17.901 --> 30:21.070
Been driving this Allah-forsaken taxi
for 30 hours.

30:21.237 --> 30:23.281
It's too much.

30:24.324 --> 30:26.201
I spent the day
waiting to see a man

30:26.367 --> 30:27.827
who will not see me.

30:27.994 --> 30:30.371
My brother-in-law hates me.

30:30.538 --> 30:32.290
I have been in America
for a week,

30:32.457 --> 30:34.459
and it has done nothing
but eat my money.

30:34.626 --> 30:36.252
- I sell nothing.
- Hmm.

30:36.419 --> 30:37.921
What do you sell?

30:38.087 --> 30:41.674
Worthless gewgaws
and baubles

30:41.841 --> 30:43.468
and tourist trinkets.

30:43.635 --> 30:46.429
It's horrible, cheap,

30:46.596 --> 30:49.349
foolish, ugly shit.

30:51.184 --> 30:53.102
- You try and sell shit?
- I sell shit, yeah.

30:53.269 --> 30:55.230
And they will not buy it?

30:55.396 --> 30:56.773
- No.
- Eh, strange.

30:56.940 --> 30:58.608
'Cause when you look
in the stores here,

30:58.775 --> 31:00.151
that's all they sell.

31:00.318 --> 31:01.819
Shit.

31:01.986 --> 31:03.446
Take Eighth Avenue.

31:03.613 --> 31:05.448
We'll go uptown that way.

32:04.799 --> 32:06.426
My grandmother...

32:07.677 --> 32:09.679
..once swore that
she had seen an ifrit,

32:09.846 --> 32:12.390
or perhaps a marid,

32:12.557 --> 32:15.310
late one evening,
on the edge of the desert.

32:16.853 --> 32:19.147
We all told her
it was just a sandstorm,

32:19.314 --> 32:22.984
a little wind,
but she had seen its face.

32:25.278 --> 32:29.490
And its eyes, like yours,
were burning flames.

32:31.117 --> 32:33.119
Grandmothers came here too.

32:34.579 --> 32:36.914
Are there many jinn in New York?

32:37.957 --> 32:39.542
No.

32:40.543 --> 32:42.086
There are angels.

32:43.755 --> 32:46.549
There are men
who Allah made from mud.

32:49.052 --> 32:51.429
Then there are
the people of the fire.

32:52.555 --> 32:53.765
The jinn.

32:53.931 --> 32:56.100
They know nothing
about my people here.

32:57.143 --> 32:59.354
They think all we do
is grant wishes.

32:59.520 --> 33:01.147
If I could grant a wish,

33:01.314 --> 33:03.232
do you think
I would be driving a cab?

33:03.399 --> 33:07.028
Once I had a man
shit in the back seat.

33:07.195 --> 33:09.781
I had to clean wet shit
from that seat.

33:09.947 --> 33:11.949
Tell me, is that right?

33:18.122 --> 33:19.707
That's not right.

34:05.253 --> 34:06.963
Keep the change.

34:22.729 --> 34:24.313
I'm in room 318.

34:28.025 --> 34:31.112
Going to 76th and Madison.

