47:57.834 --> 47:59.545
not with the current state
of my luck.

47:59.711 --> 48:01.338
This cunt's got my coin.

48:02.548 --> 48:04.424
Give me my coin, cunt.

48:04.591 --> 48:08.053
- The coin you gave me?
- Witness. He has a point.

48:09.096 --> 48:10.639
I gave you the wrong coin.

48:10.806 --> 48:12.891
The one I gave you
was my lucky coin.

48:13.058 --> 48:16.562
Well, you can't afford to be
too careless with a lucky coin.

48:16.728 --> 48:18.772
Something like that,
you wanna hang on to.

48:18.939 --> 48:22.192
Tell you what, I'll give you
your lucky coin back

48:22.359 --> 48:25.028
when you tell me
how you plucked it out of thin air.

48:25.195 --> 48:26.905
I plucked it out of thin air

48:27.072 --> 48:30.075
is how I plucked it out of thin air,
ya bug-eatin' nonce.

48:31.493 --> 48:35.330
Now give me...my...coin.

48:35.497 --> 48:39.084
I threw it...away.

48:39.251 --> 48:43.297
Where...did you throw it...away?

48:45.632 --> 48:47.676
Eagle Point, Indiana.

48:50.053 --> 48:52.931
So, if you want
your lucky coin back,

48:53.098 --> 48:55.350
make your way
to Parkview Cemetery.

48:55.517 --> 48:57.436
There you will find
my wife's grave

48:57.603 --> 48:59.187
with your coin on top.

48:59.354 --> 49:01.023
Oh, you fucker.

49:02.691 --> 49:04.818
Suppose I'll just be one more
in a long line of men

49:04.985 --> 49:06.820
to climb on top
of your dead wife.

49:06.987 --> 49:08.655
Be nice.

49:10.490 --> 49:12.784
- I'll see you in Wisconsin.
- Yeah.

49:13.910 --> 49:16.330
Good luck,
Mad Sweeney.

49:16.496 --> 49:18.081
I'll see you back at the car.

49:18.248 --> 49:20.000
Just make sure
he doesn't steal it.

49:28.842 --> 49:30.761
Now, you're gonna do
a little light shopping

49:30.927 --> 49:32.304
at the grocery store.

49:32.471 --> 49:34.181
Pass a little time
at the phone booth.

49:34.348 --> 49:35.849
If anybody asks you
what you're doing,

49:36.016 --> 49:37.893
well, you're waiting for
a call from your girlfriend.

49:38.060 --> 49:39.311
Her car broke down.

49:39.478 --> 49:40.937
Here.

49:41.104 --> 49:44.441
- Who the fuck is this?
- You the fuck is this.

49:45.525 --> 49:48.070
"A. Haddock, Director of Security,
A1 Security Services."

49:48.236 --> 49:49.696
Yeah, that's you.

49:49.863 --> 49:51.365
But what's the 'A' stand for?

49:51.531 --> 49:54.451
Alberto? Alphonse? Augustine?

49:54.618 --> 49:56.203
Ambrose?
It's entirely up to you.

49:56.370 --> 49:58.538
'Asshole' is what I feel like.

49:58.705 --> 50:00.207
Nice to meet you, Asshole.

50:00.374 --> 50:02.084
I'm James O'Gorman.
Jimmy to my friends.

50:02.250 --> 50:04.044
I got a card too.

50:04.211 --> 50:07.172
OK. Let's get outta here.

50:07.339 --> 50:08.715
Huh? Alright.

50:10.425 --> 50:11.885
I'm gonna leave you
with one question.

50:12.052 --> 50:14.221
If at the end of this night
you do not end up in jail,

50:14.388 --> 50:16.098
will you believe in me?

50:17.557 --> 50:19.559
Don't answer that question.

51:16.950 --> 51:19.286
No. No, no, no, no, no.

51:21.663 --> 51:23.749
Fuck!

51:46.772 --> 51:48.148
A1 Security Services.

51:48.315 --> 51:50.192
<i>Can I speak to A. Haddock?</i>

51:50.358 --> 51:51.777
Uh, this is Andy Haddock.

51:51.943 --> 51:53.612
<i>Mr Haddock,
this is the Chicago Police.</i>

51:53.779 --> 51:55.363
<i>You've got a man
at the First River Bank</i>

51:55.530 --> 51:57.199
<i>on the corner
of Market and Second?</i>

51:57.365 --> 51:59.201
Uh...yeah.
That's...that's right, Officer.

51:59.367 --> 52:03.038
It...it should be James O'Gorman.
Is there a problem?

52:03.205 --> 52:04.414
<i>No problem, sir.</i>

52:04.581 --> 52:06.166
<i>Just wanted to make sure
everything's in order.</i>

52:06.333 --> 52:07.793
- Well, thank you.
<i>- We're just concerned.</i>

52:07.959 --> 52:09.628
<i>Because something like this
really ought to be handled</i>

52:09.795 --> 52:11.171
<i>by two personnel.</i>

52:11.338 --> 52:12.714
Oh, tell me about it!

52:12.881 --> 52:14.591
Better yet, you tell
those stingy bastards

52:14.758 --> 52:16.301
down at First River Bank
about it.

52:16.468 --> 52:18.303
I mean, these are my men
I'm putting on the line.

52:18.470 --> 52:19.805
You know, they're good men.

52:19.971 --> 52:24.434
You know, you sound like
a bright young man, Officer...?

52:24.601 --> 52:26.978
<i>- Myerson.</i>
- Officer Myerson.

52:28.063 --> 52:30.190
If you ever need
any extra weekend work,

52:30.357 --> 52:32.025
you just give us a call.

52:32.192 --> 52:33.735
- You got my card?
<i>- Yes, sir.</i>

52:33.902 --> 52:36.822
- Hang onto it. You call us.
<i>- Yes, sir.</i>

52:36.988 --> 52:38.865
<i>Have a good evening, sir.</i>

52:46.706 --> 52:48.917
So that's what you do
to make money.

52:49.084 --> 52:51.253
You believe in me now?

52:52.295 --> 52:53.880
I believe you exist.

52:54.047 --> 52:56.842
Oh, I think I deserve
a little more faith than that.

52:57.008 --> 52:58.468
Are you back in jail?

52:58.635 --> 53:00.554
All that whining
about going back to jail,

53:00.720 --> 53:02.347
and you haven't, have you?

53:02.514 --> 53:04.641
Not yet.

53:10.188 --> 53:12.691
This is
the only country in the world

53:12.858 --> 53:15.110
that wonders what it is.

53:15.277 --> 53:17.529
You've been to a lot of
other countries, have you?

53:17.696 --> 53:19.823
No. No, never, just this one.

53:20.907 --> 53:22.826
Just that the others
know what they are.

53:22.993 --> 53:26.162
I mean, no-one wonders
about the heart of Norway

53:26.329 --> 53:28.540
or goes searching
for the soul of Mozambique.

53:28.707 --> 53:30.542
Mozambique knows what it is.

53:30.709 --> 53:32.252
They all know what they are.

53:32.419 --> 53:33.879
Americans know who they are.

53:34.045 --> 53:35.422
They pretend they know.

53:35.589 --> 53:37.007
But it's still
just pretending.

53:37.173 --> 53:39.175
Like I'm pretending now.
Just like you.

53:39.342 --> 53:41.553
What am I pretending?

53:42.596 --> 53:47.475
You are pretending you cannot
believe in impossible things.

53:50.270 --> 53:54.149
Uh, I'd be genuinely deluded
if I believed that shit.

53:54.316 --> 53:56.443
If you are deluded,
I believe it's genuine.

53:56.610 --> 54:00.447
You don't strike me
as the disingenuous type.

54:19.549 --> 54:21.217
OK, let's go.

54:23.470 --> 54:25.931
Huh?

54:26.097 --> 54:28.224
Did I make snow?

54:29.643 --> 54:31.937
Did you make snow?

54:37.025 --> 54:39.903
Well, if you choose
to believe you made snow,

54:40.070 --> 54:43.156
then you get to live
the rest of your life believing

54:43.323 --> 54:46.451
that you can do things
that are impossible.

54:47.535 --> 54:49.454
Or you can believe
it's a delusion.

54:49.621 --> 54:51.706
No, see,
delusions feel real, OK?

54:51.873 --> 54:54.000
That's why it's a delusion.
None of this feels real.

54:54.167 --> 54:55.877
It feels like a dream.

54:56.920 --> 54:59.506
What a beautiful,
beautiful thing

54:59.673 --> 55:02.217
to be able to dream
when you're not asleep.

55:05.136 --> 55:06.805
I've...

55:06.972 --> 55:08.682
I've crossed enough paths

55:08.848 --> 55:11.267
to know that one in four people
are rock stupid.

55:11.434 --> 55:13.687
Even the smart ones have got
some kind of delusion

55:13.853 --> 55:17.023
they believe in,
whether it's gods or ghosts.

55:21.194 --> 55:23.029
Do you believe in love?

55:23.196 --> 55:25.323
Yeah, I believe the shit
out of love.

55:25.490 --> 55:27.158
Did you always?

55:28.576 --> 55:29.995
Not before Laura.

55:30.161 --> 55:32.372
So you didn't believe
till you did,

55:32.539 --> 55:35.083
and then the world changed
because you believed.

55:35.250 --> 55:38.586
Belief is only a product
of the company we keep

55:38.753 --> 55:40.964
and how easily we scare.

55:41.131 --> 55:42.882
And you do not scare easily.

55:43.049 --> 55:46.636
And my company is questionable.

55:46.803 --> 55:48.388
Always has been.

55:52.100 --> 55:56.271
The only thing that scares me
is being forgotten.

55:57.313 --> 55:59.733
I can survive most things,
but not that.

56:00.942 --> 56:03.987
Very best part
of memory is it's...

56:04.154 --> 56:06.072
..mostly about forgetting.

56:06.239 --> 56:09.951
We remember
what's important to us.

56:11.369 --> 56:13.288
I wonder what'll be
the first thing

56:13.455 --> 56:14.914
that drifts through your mind

56:15.081 --> 56:16.833
when you look back
on this evening?

56:18.293 --> 56:21.713
Snow, I bet.

